President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Brett H. McGurk as the Ambassador to the Republic of Iraq and Michele J. Sison as the Ambassador to the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka and the Republic of Maldives. McGurk currently serves as a senior advisor to the U.S. Ambassador to Iraq and has previous experience working in various roles in Iraq and Afghanistan. Sison is currently the Assistant Chief of Mission for Law Enforcement and Rule of Law Assistance in Baghdad, Iraq and has previously served as Ambassador to Lebanon and the United Arab Emirates. She has also held various assignments in countries such as Pakistan, India, Cameroon, and Haiti.